<br>
&quot;Can I get ye anythin'?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Normally, I would say no, but today I will have some of your Elven wine,&quot; Enoch responds with a sigh.<br>
<br>
As the barmaid is filling his order, Enoch trys to gather his thoughts and make some since of the past two days.<br>
<br>
&quot;Here ye go,&quot; the barmaid places the drink in front of him. She must sense that he is overly troubled today as she is careful to not startle the slender elf. &quot;Is there somethin' botherin' ye today?&quot;<br>
<br>
Enoch looks up, and starts to dismiss the question, but today is different and he decides to attempt to tell his story. &quot;Aye, as a matter of fact there are many thoughts cluttering my head today.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Go on,&quot; the barmaid leads.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, it all started yesterday. I awoke in my bed, in Felwithe. Now, that in itself may not be strange, except that I have nae been to that room in over fifty years. I first thought that perhaps some evil majik had brought me there or maybe I was still asleep and dreaming of my childhood. But now, it has become apparent that something far different has occured.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why is that?&quot; the barmaid inquires.<br>
<br>
&quot;I suppose what I may say next may sound extrodinarily strange . . .but I was once a very powerful wizard. Looking at me now, you would nae think there was any power in me at all, and you would be very correct. I was once able to call down fire and ice from the skies. Spells so powerful that few could withstand them. Yet, yesterday I could not even start a fire in the hearth to warm the room.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ye may think me a madman for saying such things, but it is true. Even more, it is as if I have returned to my youth. People that I once knew as friends, now great me as they would a stranger, as if they do not even know me. Others from my youth call me by Enochi, a name that I have not used since I entered the wizard guild in Felwithe. I keep thinking that it is all a dream, but I have yet to awaken.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That is a strange tale ya have indeed, perhaps you have been given a second chance,&quot; the barmaid replies with a knowing smile.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aye, perhaps,&quot; Enochi ponders.  <p>Enoch Spellweaver
